title: For Sale:  Daewoo DR-300
postcontent: Korean Daewoo DR300 rifle in 7.62x39 cal, (same as the AK47). This is an awesome rifle with awesome 30 caliber power!! It uses AR 16 7.62x39 magazines. The rifle is in almost new condition. I have fired 20 rounds through it. I purchased this for my collection and it has sat in my safe for too long. Priorities change. Time for someone else to enjoy it. The Daewoo is one of the best designed semi-auto rifles that I have ever encountered. It utilizes the gas piston system of the AK47 and the bolt and receiver of similar design of the AR15. The Lower was made by Kimber. This rifle uses the AR 15 trigger group, so replacement parts for the fire control group are not an issue. That along with the chrome-lined barrel help make this probably the most accurate 7.62x39 rifle you will ever fire. This rifle comes with 1 30 round magazine, 2 10 round  magazines, factory field cleaning kit and 120 rounds of Wolf 122 grain FMJ Ammunition in a hard rifle case. This is a fairly rare rifle with a low serial number. You will hardly ever see one of these for sale. Reason being once you own one you never want to get rid of it. They are just that good. Asking price is $1500.00 cash or best offer. Will consider all trade offers. Looking to trade for 5.56 AR-15.

postcontent:
Anaconda .44 magnum in stainless steel with an 8" barrel with original papers and case in great condition. The "snakes" are getting hard to find, especially in an 8" barrel. 
The Anaconda holds six rounds and weighs 59 oz. It was originally introduced in 1990 & is chambered for the .44 Magnum cartridge. Colt has billed this pistol as among the most accurate .44 Magnum revolvers in production. Its fit and finish resembled an up-sized King Cobra married to a ventilated-rib barrel reminiscent of the Python's. Initially marketed with a satin brushed stainless finish, Anacondas came equipped with four, six, or eight inch barrels, neoprene synthetic rubber finger-grooved combat-style grips with nickel colored 'Rampant Colt' medallions, large target type hammers and triggers, as well as open iron sights with a red insert front and fully adjustable white outline rear. The trigger actions on these guns are rated as very high-quality, and the heavy-duty solid construction and weight tends to absorb recoil, making the Anaconda relatively easy to shoot with heavy loads.
For buyer not local West Plains, MO, would require that the transaction be completed by shipping through an FFL. I have a purchase agreement that I will sign and have notorized that will give the details of the transaction. Buyer can pick his choice of an FFL local to me and I will leave the pistol with them. Buyer can then call them and give instructions for how things will be done and I will also leave a copy of the purchase agreement with them that will give detailed instructions about how things should be handled. After buyer is able to verify that the FFL has the pistol, he will then send them a cashier's check for the purchase price. After the FFL receives the funds they will ship the pistol out. This will protect both buyer and seller and will ensure a smooth transaction.
